The paper deals with modeling and learning from ranking data, which is a common problem in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper also leverages recent progress in discrete choice modeling, which is a subfield of machine learning and optimization. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science), and cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
